  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">START 2018 Flooding response in Kongoussi and nearby areas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Voucher distribution for NFI ,for food  and for school supplies
-Latrines cleaning kits  implementation for sites hosting flood-affected people (i.e. schools): buckets, broomstick, brushes, gloves and protection items, bleach) 
-Waste disposal at the site hosting the flood affected people (i.e. schools): mobile latrines and mobiles showers)
-Menstrual management kits distribution
-Mass awareness activities (during kit distribution)
-Household water treatment and mosquito nets
-PDM</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to provide emergency assistance to all 2,168 affected people affected directly by flooding in Kongoussi and in the 6 surrounding villages of Birou, Bognam, Loaga, Rissia, Sanrgo and Sakou. Our rapid deployment of 45-day project will contribute to saving lives by providing immediate needs.</narrative>
  </description>
